    "instruction": "For each component in [\"carts\", \"catalogue\", \"orders\", \"payment\", \"user\"] do the following using metric.csv and log.csv:\n1) For kpi_name in [\"workload\", \"cpu\"] compute global P95 over the full series (do NOT filter by window). Then filter metric rows to the incident window [2024-01-20 14:33:22 UTC, 2024-01-20 15:03:22 UTC] and for each (cmdb_id, kpi_name) return: cmdb_id, kpi_name, p95_threshold, count_points_in_window, count_points_exceeding_p95 (value > p95_threshold), earliest_timestamp_exceeding_p95_in_window (ISO string or null), max_value_in_window.\n2) From log.csv, filter to the same incident window and for these five components compute per-component: cmdb_id, sum_log_row_count, sum_log_error_count, number_of_log_rows_in_window.\nReturn a JSON object with keys: 'workload_cpu_anomalies' (list of the metric rows from step 1; limit to these 10 rows), 'candidate_logs' (list of the 5 component log summaries). Keep outputs compact and use ISO timestamps for earliest timestamps. If a KPI is not present for a component, include it with counts zero and null earliest timestamp."
